<span id="freeTextContainer6763375380095726219">I really enjoyed this book. I loved the author’s writing style and really connected to the main character, Elisabetta. I was on the road to giving it a rare five stars...until I reached part 3. Part 3 of the book basically renders Lisa’s entire relationship with Giuliano pointless, and the ending was so unsatisfactory that I just stared at the book afterwards for like 5 minutes. It’s worth the read, though.</span>

          </span>
